{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to speak today about the relationship"},{"time":3000,"text":"between science and human values."},{"time":7000,"text":"Now, it's generally understood that"},{"time":9000,"text":"questions of morality --"},{"time":11000,"text":"questions of good and evil and right and wrong --"},{"time":13000,"text":"are questions about which science officially has no opinion."},{"time":16000,"text":"It's thought that science can help us"},{"time":19000,"text":"get what we value,"},{"time":21000,"text":"but it can never tell us what we ought to value."},{"time":24000,"text":"And, consequently, most people -- I think most people"},{"time":26000,"text":"probably here -- think that science will never answer"},{"time":29000,"text":"the most important questions in human life:"},{"time":32000,"text":"questions like, \"What is worth living for?\""},{"time":34000,"text":"\"What is worth dying for?\""},{"time":36000,"text":"\"What constitutes a good life?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"So, I'm going to argue"},{"time":40000,"text":"that this is an illusion -- that the separation between"},{"time":42000,"text":"science and human values is an illusion --"},{"time":44000,"text":"and actually quite a dangerous one"},{"time":47000,"text":"at this point in human history."},{"time":49000,"text":"Now, it's often said that science"},{"time":51000,"text":"cannot give us a foundation for morality and human values,"},{"time":54000,"text":"because science deals with facts,"},{"time":57000,"text":"and facts and values seem to belong to different spheres."},{"time":61000,"text":"It's often thought that there's no description"},{"time":64000,"text":"of the way the world is"},{"time":66000,"text":"that can tell us how the world ought to be."},{"time":70000,"text":"But I think this is quite clearly untrue."},{"time":72000,"text":"Values are a certain kind of fact."},{"time":76000,"text":"They are facts about the well-being of conscious creatures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"Why is it that we don't have ethical obligations toward rocks?"},{"time":84000,"text":"Why don't we feel compassion for rocks?"},{"time":87000,"text":"It's because we don't think rocks can suffer. And if we're more"},{"time":89000,"text":"concerned about our fellow primates"},{"time":91000,"text":"than we are about insects, as indeed we are,"},{"time":94000,"text":"it's because we think they're exposed to a greater range"},{"time":96000,"text":"of potential happiness and suffering."},{"time":99000,"text":"Now, the crucial thing to notice here"},{"time":102000,"text":"is that this is a factual claim:"},{"time":104000,"text":"This is something that we could be right or wrong about. And if we"},{"time":106000,"text":"have misconstrued the relationship between biological complexity"},{"time":109000,"text":"and the possibilities of experience"},{"time":112000,"text":"well then we could be wrong about the inner lives of insects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"And there's no notion,"},{"time":119000,"text":"no version of human morality"},{"time":121000,"text":"and human values that I've ever come across"},{"time":124000,"text":"that is not at some point reducible"},{"time":126000,"text":"to a concern about conscious experience"},{"time":129000,"text":"and its possible changes."},{"time":131000,"text":"Even if you get your values from religion,"},{"time":134000,"text":"even if you think that good and evil ultimately"},{"time":136000,"text":"relate to conditions after death --"},{"time":138000,"text":"either to an eternity of happiness with God"},{"time":141000,"text":"or an eternity of suffering in hell --"},{"time":143000,"text":"you are still concerned about consciousness and its changes."},{"time":147000,"text":"And to say that such changes can persist after death"},{"time":150000,"text":"is itself a factual claim,"},{"time":152000,"text":"which, of course, may or may not be true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155000,"text":"Now, to speak about the conditions of well-being"},{"time":158000,"text":"in this life, for human beings,"},{"time":160000,"text":"we know that there is a continuum of such facts."},{"time":163000,"text":"We know that it's possible to live in a failed state,"},{"time":166000,"text":"where everything that can go wrong does go wrong --"},{"time":168000,"text":"where mothers cannot feed their children,"},{"time":171000,"text":"where strangers cannot find the basis for peaceful collaboration,"},{"time":175000,"text":"where people are murdered indiscriminately."},{"time":178000,"text":"And we know that it's possible to move along this continuum"},{"time":181000,"text":"towards something quite a bit more idyllic,"},{"time":183000,"text":"to a place where a conference like this is even conceivable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"And we know -- we know --"},{"time":191000,"text":"that there are right and wrong answers"},{"time":193000,"text":"to how to move in this space."},{"time":195000,"text":"Would adding cholera to the water be a good idea?"},{"time":201000,"text":"Probably not."},{"time":203000,"text":"Would it be a good idea for everyone to believe in the evil eye,"},{"time":206000,"text":"so that when bad things happened to them"},{"time":208000,"text":"they immediately blame their neighbors? Probably not."},{"time":212000,"text":"There are truths to be known"},{"time":214000,"text":"about how human communities flourish,"},{"time":217000,"text":"whether or not we understand these truths."},{"time":219000,"text":"And morality relates to these truths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"So, in talking about values we are talking about facts."},{"time":226000,"text":"Now, of course our situation in the world can be understood at many levels --"},{"time":229000,"text":"from the level of the genome"},{"time":231000,"text":"on up to the level of economic systems"},{"time":233000,"text":"and political arrangements."},{"time":235000,"text":"But if we're going to talk about human well-being"},{"time":237000,"text":"we are, of necessity, talking about the human brain."},{"time":240000,"text":"Because we know that our experience of the world and of ourselves within it"},{"time":243000,"text":"is realized in the brain --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246000,"text":"whatever happens after death."},{"time":248000,"text":"Even if the suicide bomber does get 72 virgins in the afterlife,"},{"time":253000,"text":"in this life, his personality --"},{"time":256000,"text":"his rather unfortunate personality --"},{"time":258000,"text":"is the product of his brain."},{"time":261000,"text":"So the contributions of culture --"},{"time":264000,"text":"if culture changes us, as indeed it does,"},{"time":266000,"text":"it changes us by changing our brains."},{"time":268000,"text":"And so therefore whatever cultural variation there is"},{"time":271000,"text":"in how human beings flourish"},{"time":273000,"text":"can, at least in principle, be understood"},{"time":275000,"text":"in the context of a maturing science of the mind --"},{"time":278000,"text":"neuroscience, psychology, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"So, what I'm arguing is that"},{"time":283000,"text":"value's reduced to facts --"},{"time":285000,"text":"to facts about the conscious experience"},{"time":287000,"text":"of conscious beings."},{"time":290000,"text":"And we can therefore visualize a space"},{"time":293000,"text":"of possible changes in the experience of these beings."},{"time":296000,"text":"And I think of this as kind of a moral landscape,"},{"time":298000,"text":"with peaks and valleys that correspond"},{"time":300000,"text":"to differences in the well-being of conscious creatures,"},{"time":303000,"text":"both personal and collective."},{"time":305000,"text":"And one thing to notice is that perhaps"},{"time":307000,"text":"there are states of human well-being"},{"time":309000,"text":"that we rarely access, that few people access."},{"time":312000,"text":"And these await our discovery."},{"time":314000,"text":"Perhaps some of these states can be appropriately called"},{"time":316000,"text":"mystical or spiritual."},{"time":318000,"text":"Perhaps there are other states that we can't access"},{"time":320000,"text":"because of how our minds are structured"},{"time":323000,"text":"but other minds possibly could access them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"Now, let me be clear about what I'm not saying. I'm not saying"},{"time":329000,"text":"that science is guaranteed to map this space,"},{"time":334000,"text":"or that we will have scientific answers to every"},{"time":336000,"text":"conceivable moral question."},{"time":338000,"text":"I don't think, for instance, that you will one day consult"},{"time":340000,"text":"a supercomputer to learn whether you should have a second child,"},{"time":344000,"text":"or whether we should bomb Iran's nuclear facilities,"},{"time":348000,"text":"or whether you can deduct the full cost of TED as a business expense."},{"time":352000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":354000,"text":"But if questions affect human well-being"},{"time":356000,"text":"then they do have answers, whether or not we can find them."},{"time":359000,"text":"And just admitting this --"},{"time":361000,"text":"just admitting that there are right and wrong answers"},{"time":363000,"text":"to the question of how humans flourish --"},{"time":365000,"text":"will change the way we talk about morality,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and will change our expectations"},{"time":369000,"text":"of human cooperation in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"For instance, there are 21 states in our country"},{"time":377000,"text":"where corporal punishment in the classroom is legal,"},{"time":380000,"text":"where it is legal for a teacher to beat a child with a wooden board, hard,"},{"time":386000,"text":"and raising large bruises and blisters and even breaking the skin."},{"time":390000,"text":"And hundreds of thousands of children, incidentally,"},{"time":392000,"text":"are subjected to this every year."},{"time":394000,"text":"The locations of these enlightened districts, I think, will fail to surprise you."},{"time":399000,"text":"We're not talking about Connecticut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"And the rationale for this behavior is explicitly religious."},{"time":406000,"text":"The creator of the universe himself"},{"time":408000,"text":"has told us not to spare the rod,"},{"time":410000,"text":"lest we spoil the child --"},{"time":412000,"text":"this is in Proverbs 13 and 20, and I believe, 23."},{"time":417000,"text":"But we can ask the obvious question:"},{"time":419000,"text":"Is it a good idea, generally speaking,"},{"time":423000,"text":"to subject children to pain"},{"time":426000,"text":"and violence and public humiliation"},{"time":429000,"text":"as a way of encouraging healthy emotional development"},{"time":431000,"text":"and good behavior?"},{"time":433000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":434000,"text":"Is there any doubt"},{"time":438000,"text":"that this question has an answer,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and that it matters?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"Now, many of you might worry"},{"time":445000,"text":"that the notion of well-being is truly undefined,"},{"time":448000,"text":"and seemingly perpetually open to be re-construed."},{"time":451000,"text":"And so, how therefore can there be an"},{"time":453000,"text":"objective notion of well-being?"},{"time":456000,"text":"Well, consider by analogy, the concept of physical health."},{"time":459000,"text":"The concept of physical health is undefined."},{"time":462000,"text":"As we just heard from Michael Specter, it has changed over the years."},{"time":465000,"text":"When this statue was carved"},{"time":467000,"text":"the average life expectancy was probably 30."},{"time":470000,"text":"It's now around 80 in the developed world."},{"time":473000,"text":"There may come a time when we meddle with our genomes"},{"time":476000,"text":"in such a way that not being able to run a marathon"},{"time":479000,"text":"at age 200 will be considered a profound disability."},{"time":483000,"text":"People will send you donations when you're in that condition."},{"time":486000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"Notice that the fact that the concept of health"},{"time":492000,"text":"is open, genuinely open for revision,"},{"time":495000,"text":"does not make it vacuous."},{"time":497000,"text":"The distinction between a healthy person"},{"time":500000,"text":"and a dead one"},{"time":502000,"text":"is about as clear and consequential as any we make in science."},{"time":508000,"text":"Another thing to notice is there may be many peaks on the moral landscape:"},{"time":511000,"text":"There may be equivalent ways to thrive;"},{"time":514000,"text":"there may be equivalent ways to organize a human society"},{"time":516000,"text":"so as to maximize human flourishing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"Now, why wouldn't this"},{"time":520000,"text":"undermine an objective morality?"},{"time":524000,"text":"Well think of how we talk about food:"},{"time":527000,"text":"I would never be tempted to argue to you"},{"time":530000,"text":"that there must be one right food to eat."},{"time":532000,"text":"There is clearly a range of materials"},{"time":534000,"text":"that constitute healthy food."},{"time":536000,"text":"But there's nevertheless a clear distinction"},{"time":538000,"text":"between food and poison."},{"time":540000,"text":"The fact that there are many right answers"},{"time":543000,"text":"to the question, \"What is food?\""},{"time":545000,"text":"does not tempt us"},{"time":548000,"text":"to say that there are no truths to be known about human nutrition."},{"time":553000,"text":"Many people worry"},{"time":555000,"text":"that a universal morality would require"},{"time":558000,"text":"moral precepts that admit of no exceptions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"So, for instance, if it's really wrong to lie,"},{"time":563000,"text":"it must always be wrong to lie,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and if you can find an exception,"},{"time":567000,"text":"well then there's no such thing as moral truth."},{"time":570000,"text":"Why would we think this?"},{"time":572000,"text":"Consider, by analogy, the game of chess."},{"time":575000,"text":"Now, if you're going to play good chess,"},{"time":577000,"text":"a principle like, \"Don't lose your Queen,\""},{"time":579000,"text":"is very good to follow."},{"time":581000,"text":"But it clearly admits some exceptions."},{"time":583000,"text":"There are moments when losing your Queen is a brilliant thing to do."},{"time":586000,"text":"There are moments when it is the only good thing you can do."},{"time":590000,"text":"And yet, chess is a domain of perfect objectivity."},{"time":594000,"text":"The fact that there are exceptions here does not"},{"time":596000,"text":"change that at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599000,"text":"Now, this brings us to the sorts of moves"},{"time":602000,"text":"that people are apt to make in the moral sphere."},{"time":605000,"text":"Consider the great problem of women's bodies:"},{"time":610000,"text":"What to do about them?"},{"time":612000,"text":"Well this is one thing you can do about them:"},{"time":614000,"text":"You can cover them up."},{"time":616000,"text":"Now, it is the position, generally speaking, of our intellectual community"},{"time":618000,"text":"that while we may not like this,"},{"time":622000,"text":"we might think of this as \"wrong\""},{"time":624000,"text":"in Boston or Palo Alto,"},{"time":626000,"text":"who are we to say"},{"time":628000,"text":"that the proud denizens of an ancient culture"},{"time":631000,"text":"are wrong to force their wives and daughters"},{"time":634000,"text":"to live in cloth bags?"},{"time":636000,"text":"And who are we to say, even, that they're wrong"},{"time":638000,"text":"to beat them with lengths of steel cable,"},{"time":640000,"text":"or throw battery acid in their faces"},{"time":642000,"text":"if they decline the privilege of being smothered in this way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"Well, who are we not to say this?"},{"time":649000,"text":"Who are we to pretend"},{"time":651000,"text":"that we know so little about human well-being"},{"time":655000,"text":"that we have to be non-judgmental about a practice like this?"},{"time":659000,"text":"I'm not talking about voluntary wearing of a veil --"},{"time":663000,"text":"women should be able to wear whatever they want, as far as I'm concerned."},{"time":665000,"text":"But what does voluntary mean"},{"time":668000,"text":"in a community where,"},{"time":670000,"text":"when a girl gets raped,"},{"time":673000,"text":"her father's first impulse,"},{"time":675000,"text":"rather often, is to murder her out of shame?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":680000,"text":"Just let that fact detonate in your brain for a minute:"},{"time":687000,"text":"Your daughter gets raped,"},{"time":689000,"text":"and what you want to do is kill her."},{"time":697000,"text":"What are the chances that represents"},{"time":699000,"text":"a peak of human flourishing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"Now, to say this is not to say that we have got the"},{"time":709000,"text":"perfect solution in our own society."},{"time":713000,"text":"For instance,"},{"time":715000,"text":"this is what it's like to go to a newsstand almost anywhere"},{"time":717000,"text":"in the civilized world."},{"time":719000,"text":"Now, granted, for many men"},{"time":721000,"text":"it may require a degree in philosophy to see something wrong with these images."},{"time":724000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":727000,"text":"But if we are in a reflective mood,"},{"time":730000,"text":"we can ask,"},{"time":732000,"text":"\"Is this the perfect expression"},{"time":734000,"text":"of psychological balance"},{"time":736000,"text":"with respect to variables like youth and beauty and women's bodies?\""},{"time":739000,"text":"I mean, is this the optimal environment"},{"time":741000,"text":"in which to raise our children?"},{"time":745000,"text":"Probably not. OK, so perhaps there's some place"},{"time":747000,"text":"on the spectrum"},{"time":749000,"text":"between these two extremes"},{"time":751000,"text":"that represents a place of better balance."},{"time":754000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":762000,"text":"Perhaps there are many such places --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"again, given other changes in human culture"},{"time":767000,"text":"there may be many peaks on the moral landscape."},{"time":769000,"text":"But the thing to notice is that there will be"},{"time":771000,"text":"many more ways not to be on a peak."},{"time":776000,"text":"Now the irony, from my perspective,"},{"time":778000,"text":"is that the only people who seem to generally agree with me"},{"time":781000,"text":"and who think that there are right and wrong answers to moral questions"},{"time":784000,"text":"are religious demagogues of one form or another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787000,"text":"And of course they think they have right answers to moral questions"},{"time":790000,"text":"because they got these answers from a voice in a whirlwind,"},{"time":794000,"text":"not because they made an intelligent analysis of the causes"},{"time":796000,"text":"and condition of human and animal well-being."},{"time":800000,"text":"In fact, the endurance of religion"},{"time":802000,"text":"as a lens through which most people view moral questions"},{"time":806000,"text":"has separated most moral talk"},{"time":809000,"text":"from real questions of human and animal suffering."},{"time":813000,"text":"This is why we spend our time"},{"time":815000,"text":"talking about things like gay marriage"},{"time":817000,"text":"and not about genocide or nuclear proliferation"},{"time":821000,"text":"or poverty or any other hugely consequential issue."},{"time":826000,"text":"But the demagogues are right about one thing: We need"},{"time":828000,"text":"a universal conception of human values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"Now, what stands in the way of this?"},{"time":834000,"text":"Well, one thing to notice is that we"},{"time":836000,"text":"do something different when talking about morality --"},{"time":838000,"text":"especially secular, academic, scientist types."},{"time":842000,"text":"When talking about morality we value differences of opinion"},{"time":845000,"text":"in a way that we don't in any other area of our lives."},{"time":848000,"text":"So, for instance the Dalai Lama gets up every morning"},{"time":850000,"text":"meditating on compassion,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and he thinks that helping other human beings is an integral component"},{"time":854000,"text":"of human happiness."},{"time":857000,"text":"On the other hand, we have someone like Ted Bundy;"},{"time":859000,"text":"Ted Bundy was very fond of abducting and raping"},{"time":861000,"text":"and torturing and killing young women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863000,"text":"So, we appear to have a genuine difference of opinion"},{"time":865000,"text":"about how to profitably use one's time."},{"time":868000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":870000,"text":"Most Western intellectuals"},{"time":872000,"text":"look at this situation"},{"time":874000,"text":"and say, \"Well, there's nothing for the Dalai Lama"},{"time":876000,"text":"to be really right about -- really right about --"},{"time":879000,"text":"or for Ted Bundy to be really wrong about"},{"time":882000,"text":"that admits of a real argument"},{"time":886000,"text":"that potentially falls within the purview of science."},{"time":889000,"text":"He likes chocolate, he likes vanilla."},{"time":892000,"text":"There's nothing that one should be able to say to the other"},{"time":895000,"text":"that should persuade the other.\""},{"time":898000,"text":"Notice that we don't do this in science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"On the left you have Edward Witten."},{"time":903000,"text":"He's a string theorist."},{"time":906000,"text":"If you ask the smartest physicists around"},{"time":908000,"text":"who is the smartest physicist around,"},{"time":910000,"text":"in my experience half of them will say Ed Witten."},{"time":913000,"text":"The other half will tell you they don't like the question."},{"time":916000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":919000,"text":"So, what would happen if I showed up at a physics conference"},{"time":923000,"text":"and said,\"String theory is bogus."},{"time":925000,"text":"It doesn't resonate with me. It's not how I chose to"},{"time":927000,"text":"view the universe at a small scale."},{"time":930000,"text":"I'm not a fan.\""},{"time":932000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":935000,"text":"Well, nothing would happen because I'm not a physicist;"},{"time":937000,"text":"I don't understand string theory."},{"time":939000,"text":"I'm the Ted Bundy of string theory."},{"time":941000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":944000,"text":"I wouldn't want to belong to any string theory club that would have me as a member."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947000,"text":"But this is just the point."},{"time":949000,"text":"Whenever we are talking about facts"},{"time":952000,"text":"certain opinions must be excluded."},{"time":954000,"text":"That is what it is to have a domain of expertise."},{"time":957000,"text":"That is what it is for knowledge to count."},{"time":960000,"text":"How have we convinced ourselves"},{"time":963000,"text":"that in the moral sphere there is no such thing as moral expertise,"},{"time":967000,"text":"or moral talent, or moral genius even?"},{"time":970000,"text":"How have we convinced ourselves"},{"time":972000,"text":"that every opinion has to count?"},{"time":974000,"text":"How have we convinced ourselves"},{"time":976000,"text":"that every culture has a point of view"},{"time":978000,"text":"on these subjects worth considering?"},{"time":981000,"text":"Does the Taliban"},{"time":983000,"text":"have a point of view on physics"},{"time":985000,"text":"that is worth considering? No."},{"time":988000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":993000,"text":"How is their ignorance any less obvious"},{"time":996000,"text":"on the subject of human well-being?"},{"time":998000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004000,"text":"So, this, I think, is what the world needs now."},{"time":1008000,"text":"It needs people like ourselves to admit"},{"time":1011000,"text":"that there are right and wrong answers"},{"time":1014000,"text":"to questions of human flourishing,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"and morality relates"},{"time":1018000,"text":"to that domain of facts."},{"time":1020000,"text":"It is possible"},{"time":1022000,"text":"for individuals, and even for whole cultures,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"to care about the wrong things,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"which is to say that it's possible for them"},{"time":1031000,"text":"to have beliefs and desires that reliably lead"},{"time":1033000,"text":"to needless human suffering."},{"time":1035000,"text":"Just admitting this will transform our discourse about morality."},{"time":1040000,"text":"We live in a world in which"},{"time":1043000,"text":"the boundaries between nations mean less and less,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"and they will one day mean nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049000,"text":"We live in a world filled with destructive technology,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"and this technology cannot be uninvented;"},{"time":1053000,"text":"it will always be easier"},{"time":1055000,"text":"to break things than to fix them."},{"time":1059000,"text":"It seems to me, therefore, patently obvious"},{"time":1061000,"text":"that we can no more"},{"time":1065000,"text":"respect and tolerate"},{"time":1067000,"text":"vast differences in notions of human well-being"},{"time":1071000,"text":"than we can respect or tolerate vast differences"},{"time":1074000,"text":"in the notions about how disease spreads,"},{"time":1077000,"text":"or in the safety standards of buildings and airplanes."},{"time":1080000,"text":"We simply must converge"},{"time":1083000,"text":"on the answers we give to the most important questions in human life."},{"time":1087000,"text":"And to do that, we have to admit that these questions have answers."},{"time":1092000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1094000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1117000,"text":"Chris Anderson: So, some combustible material there."},{"time":1121000,"text":"Whether in this audience or people elsewhere in the world,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"hearing some of this, may well be doing the"},{"time":1126000,"text":"screaming-with-rage thing, after as well, some of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131000,"text":"Language seems to be really important here."},{"time":1133000,"text":"When you're talking about the veil,"},{"time":1135000,"text":"you're talking about women dressed in cloth bags."},{"time":1138000,"text":"I've lived in the Muslim world, spoken with a lot of Muslim women."},{"time":1142000,"text":"And some of them would say something else. They would say,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"\"No, you know, this is a celebration"},{"time":1147000,"text":"of female specialness,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"it helps build that and it's a result of the fact that\" --"},{"time":1152000,"text":"and this is arguably a sophisticated psychological view --"},{"time":1156000,"text":"\"that male lust is not to be trusted.\""},{"time":1159000,"text":"I mean, can you engage in a conversation"},{"time":1162000,"text":"with that kind of woman without seeming kind of cultural imperialist?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1167000,"text":"Sam Harris: Yeah, well I think I tried to broach this in a sentence,"},{"time":1170000,"text":"watching the clock ticking,"},{"time":1172000,"text":"but the question is:"},{"time":1174000,"text":"What is voluntary in a context"},{"time":1177000,"text":"where men have certain expectations,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"and you're guaranteed to be treated in a certain way"},{"time":1183000,"text":"if you don't veil yourself?"},{"time":1185000,"text":"And so, if anyone in this room"},{"time":1187000,"text":"wanted to wear a veil,"},{"time":1189000,"text":"or a very funny hat, or tattoo their face --"},{"time":1192000,"text":"I think we should be free to voluntarily do whatever we want,"},{"time":1195000,"text":"but we have to be honest about"},{"time":1198000,"text":"the constraints that these women are placed under."},{"time":1200000,"text":"And so I think we shouldn't be so eager"},{"time":1203000,"text":"to always take their word for it,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"especially when it's 120 degrees out"},{"time":1207000,"text":"and you're wearing a full burqa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1210000,"text":"CA: A lot of people want to believe in this"},{"time":1212000,"text":"concept of moral progress."},{"time":1214000,"text":"But can you reconcile that?"},{"time":1216000,"text":"I think I understood you to say that you could"},{"time":1218000,"text":"reconcile that with a world that doesn't become"},{"time":1220000,"text":"one dimensional, where we all have to think the same."},{"time":1223000,"text":"Paint your picture of what"},{"time":1225000,"text":"rolling the clock 50 years forward,"},{"time":1228000,"text":"100 years forward, how you would like to think of"},{"time":1230000,"text":"the world, balancing moral progress"},{"time":1233000,"text":"with richness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1236000,"text":"SH: Well, I think once you admit"},{"time":1238000,"text":"that we are on the path toward understanding our minds"},{"time":1241000,"text":"at the level of the brain in some important detail,"},{"time":1244000,"text":"then you have to admit"},{"time":1246000,"text":"that we are going to understand all of the positive"},{"time":1250000,"text":"and negative qualities"},{"time":1252000,"text":"of ourselves in much greater detail."},{"time":1254000,"text":"So, we're going to understand positive social emotion"},{"time":1256000,"text":"like empathy and compassion,"},{"time":1258000,"text":"and we're going to understand the factors"},{"time":1260000,"text":"that encourage it -- whether they're genetic,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"whether they're how people talk to one another,"},{"time":1264000,"text":"whether they're economic systems,"},{"time":1266000,"text":"and insofar as we begin to shine light on that"},{"time":1269000,"text":"we are inevitably going to converge"},{"time":1271000,"text":"on that fact space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1273000,"text":"So, everything is not going to be up for grabs."},{"time":1275000,"text":"It's not going to be like"},{"time":1278000,"text":"veiling my daughter from birth"},{"time":1280000,"text":"is just as good as teaching her"},{"time":1283000,"text":"to be confident and well-educated"},{"time":1287000,"text":"in the context of men who do desire women."},{"time":1290000,"text":"I mean I don't think we need an NSF grant to know"},{"time":1294000,"text":"that compulsory veiling is a bad idea --"},{"time":1297000,"text":"but at a certain point"},{"time":1299000,"text":"we're going to be able to scan the brains of everyone involved"},{"time":1302000,"text":"and actually interrogate them."},{"time":1305000,"text":"Do people love their daughters"},{"time":1308000,"text":"just as much in these systems?"},{"time":1311000,"text":"And I think there are clearly right answers to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313000,"text":"CA: And if the results come out that actually they do,"},{"time":1316000,"text":"are you prepared to shift your instinctive current judgment"},{"time":1319000,"text":"on some of these issues?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1321000,"text":"SH: Well yeah, modulo one obvious fact,"},{"time":1324000,"text":"that you can love someone"},{"time":1326000,"text":"in the context of a truly delusional belief system."},{"time":1329000,"text":"So, you can say like, \"Because I knew my gay son"},{"time":1331000,"text":"was going to go to hell if he found a boyfriend,"},{"time":1334000,"text":"I chopped his head off. And that was the most compassionate thing I could do.\""},{"time":1337000,"text":"If you get all those parts aligned,"},{"time":1339000,"text":"yes I think you could probably be feeling the emotion of love."},{"time":1342000,"text":"But again, then we have to talk about"},{"time":1344000,"text":"well-being in a larger context."},{"time":1346000,"text":"It's all of us in this together,"},{"time":1348000,"text":"not one man feeling ecstasy"},{"time":1352000,"text":"and then blowing himself up on a bus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1354000,"text":"CA: Sam, this is a conversation I would actually love to"},{"time":1356000,"text":"continue for hours."},{"time":1358000,"text":"We don't have that, but maybe another time. Thank you for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1360000,"text":"SH: Really an honor. Thank you."},{"time":1362000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}